snippet: The election of a Sunni head of Parliament could provide a political breakthrough, paving the way for a Shiite prime minister.
abstract: Iraqi lawmakers elect moderate Sunni Islamist Salim al-Jubouri as Parliament speaker, taking a small but crucial step toward ending political deadlock that has frozen decision making as military victories by Sunni militants threaten country’s existence; decision represents something of a breakthrough since it starts clock for setting up entire government.

byline.original: By ALISSA J. RUBIN and SUADAD AL-SALHY
byline.contributor: An employee of The New York Times contributed reporting from Salahuddin, Iraq.

lead_paragraph: The election of a Sunni head of Parliament could provide a political breakthrough, paving the way for a Shiite prime minister.

headline.main: Iraqi Parliament Elects Speaker in Effort to Form New Government
headline.print_headline: Election of Iraq Parliament Speaker Starts Clock on Forming New Government
